Date: Sat, 4 Jul 2026 11:13:33 +0200
Subject: [ARCHEOLOGY] sunxi: pin mmc and i2c controllers to active to break
 circular PM deadlock (#10120)

> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > Kernel v7.0 introduced runtime PM suspend capabilities for both Allwinner
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > sunxi-mmc and mv64xxx I2C controllers. During system frequency scaling (DVFS),
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > this setup introduces a critical circular dependency deadlock:
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > 1. The cpufreq governor holds the global clock lock (clk_prepare_lock)
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > to scale the CPU PLL.
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > 2. To scale CPU voltage, cpufreq writes to the AXP PMIC over I2C,
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > triggering a resume of the runtime-suspended I2C host controller.
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > 3. The I2C host controller resume path calls clk_prepare(), which blocks
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > waiting on clk_prepare_lock.
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > 4. Concurrently, a systemd runtime suspend worker blocks trying to acquire
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > clk_prepare_lock to suspend the MMC host controller.
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > This circular dependency results in immediate kernel hangs and RCU stalls.
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > Upstream megi/orange-pi-7.0 carried a legacy 145-line patch (0016-mmc-sunxi-mmc-Remove-runtime-PM.patch)
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > that completely stripped runtime PM out of the sunxi-mmc driver. However, this
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > approach was insufficient as the direct two-way deadlock between the cpufreq governor and the
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > I2C controller remained active whenever the I2C host entered runtime suspend.
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > We drop the intrusive MMC-only PM removal patch and instead break the deadlock
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > robustly by pinning both the sunxi-mmc and mv64xxx I2C controllers to their active
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > states using pm_runtime_get_sync() during driver probe. This approach keeps both
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > controllers awake, completely avoiding runtime suspend operations that collide with
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > global clock locks during voltage scaling, while keeping the driver source changes
> X-Git-Archeology: > recovered message: > to a clean, non-intrusive 1-line addition per driver.
